Citation.sTitle: Density and viscosity of pyridinium-based ionic liquids and their binary mixtures with water at several temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of two pyridinium-based ionic liquids, 1-butylpyridinium tetrafluoroborate [BuPy][BF4] and 1-octylpyridinium tetrafluoroborate [OcPy][BF4], and their binaries with water at atmospheric pressure and temperatures from (283.15 to 348.15) K were determined. The densities and viscosities of pure ionic liquids were correlated successfully by empirical equations. The Vogel Fulcher Tammann equations can fit the experimental viscosities for pure and binary of both IL systems. Excess molar volume and viscosity deviation were calculated for the binaries. The excess molar volumes have positive deviation from ideal solution while the viscosity deviations have negative values.
